    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a driver-spec 2011 BMW M3 featuring the legendary S65 4.0L V8 engine mated to a precise 6-speed manual transmission. This naturally aspirated power plant utilizes eight individual throttle bodies to deliver a linear torque curve and a visceral 8,400 RPM redline. The chassis is equipped with an M-Variable differential lock, ensuring optimal power distribution across the rear axle. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including rod bearing replacement with high-durability shells and upgraded throttle actuators. The suspension retains its factory-tuned kinematics, offering exceptional lateral grip and communicative feedback through the hydraulic steering rack. While the finish shows minor road-derived patina, the mechanical synchronization and subframe integrity remain excellent. A well-sorted example for the purist seeking an analog performance benchmark.",
